			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	JOB DESCRIPTION<br />
	We are looking for THE BEST e-commerce software developer, architect, and manager, in one. To be qualified you must have deep experience in software design and engineering, specifically for use in online, retail sales. You must be extremely driven and possess a desire to see your application produce sales and your team product incredible software.</p>
<p>
	As our new Manager of e-Commerce Application Development, you will be expected to create and drive the key architecture in and around our e-tail systems; manage a team of currently five developers (and growing); write lots of code; understand complex systems; partner with business stakeholders to develop functional specifications; drive development, oversee deployment; and, actively ensure the highest quality code, testing, and usage experience. You must stay abreast of the latest technologies and methodologies related to online retail, general web application development, and general software development.<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	KEY RESPONSIBILITIES<br />
	&bull; Leading e-commerce technology initiatives including web site development, ERP integration, customer service integration, and marketing programs.<br />
	&bull; Architecting site technology, particularly to enhance catalog management, shopping experience, user community, marketing capabilities, and scalability.<br />
	&bull; Actively managing the e-commerce application development team to ensure they write amazing code and documentation and are using the best principles you help to set.<br />
	&bull; Writing amazing code and even better documentation<br />
	&bull; Working closely with VP of Technology to achieve the business&rsquo; strategy and objectives<br />
	&bull; Working with key external vendors and partners</p>
<p>
	KEY QUALIFICATIONS<br />
	&bull; 7+ Years Software Development in Java<br />
	&bull; 7+ Years Relational Database Experience (be a data master)<br />
	&bull; 4+ Years E-Commerce Software Development (consumer retail strongly preferred)<br />
	&bull; 4+ Software Architecture Experience<br />
	&bull; 4+ Years Tomcat Application Server<br />
	&bull; 4+ Years JavaScript<br />
	&bull; 2+ Years Spring Framework<br />
	&bull; 2+ Years Team Management<br />
	&bull; Incredible understanding of the Internet, from culture to technology<br />
	&bull; Great communication skills (oral and written)</p>
<p>
	CHARACTERISTICS<br />
	&bull; Perfectly comfortable in Windows, OS X, or Linux<br />
	&bull; Experience developing high quality test plans<br />
	&bull; Diligent approach to documentation and code control<br />
	&bull; Strong problem solving and troubleshooting skills; creative solutions development<br />
	&bull; Experience with Opentaps, OFBiz platforms a serious plus<br />
	&bull; Experience with ERP implementations helpful<br />
	&bull; Experience working in high transaction environments and web sites<br />
	&bull; Experience with scaling techniques: load balancing, caching, optimization, etc.<br />
	&bull; Great knowledge of open source universe<br />
	&bull; Excellent organizational skills<br />
	&bull; Experience managing other developers and being a wonderful teammate<br />
	&bull; Experience working on community sites<br />
