	JOB DESCRIPTION<br />
	Folica.com is the best place in the world to find and buy hair products, and one of the most successful privately-held consumer e-commerce companies in the US.</p>
<p>
	We&rsquo;re looking for a professional who knows the ins and outs of web analytics (and has experience working with Omniture Site Catalyst, Coremetrics, Google Analytics or something comparable) to help us optimize every inch of Folica.com. The position is a full time role in our New York City office. You will report to the VP of Product Development and interact at all levels of the company.</p>
<p>
	Responsibilities:<br />
	&bull; Analyze and design reports that quantify site activity<br />
	&bull; Identify conversion trends and highlight opportunities for growth<br />
	&bull; Develop hypotheses for multivariate testing and optimization<br />
	&bull; Implement tests, measure results and draw smart conclusions that inform site development.<br />
	<br />
	Requirements:<br />
	&bull; 1 to 3 years experience. You have a deep understanding of a web analytics package and aren&rsquo;t afraid to use it. We prefer Omniture Site Catalyst but we&rsquo;ll take a deep understanding of Google Analytics or a comparable analytics package, too.)<br />
	&bull; You have demonstrated success in optimizing online experiences using analytics.<br />
	&bull; You&rsquo;re analytical when it comes to data and creative when it comes to testing.<br />
	&bull; You won&rsquo;t sleep until the problem&rsquo;s solved.<br />
	&bull; You get a charge out of making a difference.</p>
<p>
	You&rsquo;ll have an edge if:<br />
	&bull; You&rsquo;ve worked for a high-volume e-commerce enterprise.<br />
	&bull; You know your hair care brands.<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
